d War.                                 It was created as an alternative to the Russian and American divisions. After the Cold                                 War the Non-Aligned Movement has continued to represent the interests of developing                                 and under-represented countries. This committee will focus on two topics: Third World                                 Debt & Disaster Recovery and Self-Determination Movements. Debt & Disaster is a key                                 issue for developing countries. Rebuilding after natural disasters becomes even more of                                 an issue when these countries are burdened by debt. Aid and disaster relief only increases                                 their debt and reliance on foreign powers – something NAM strives to reduce. Popular                                 NAM policies are in opposition to the United States and other world bloc powers and                                 to the furthering of self-determination. These concepts would come into play as the                                 committee focuses on the topic of self-determination, especially in regards to Puerto                                 Rico and Western Sahara.</p>                        </div>                    </div>                </div>                <div class = "clear">                </div>            </div>            </div>        </div>    </body></html>